where \(a\) represents the maximum absolute value of the output range of the activation function. Specifically, for the Tanh function, \(a\) is equal to 1. \(t\) lies in \([0,1)\). The large value of this metric indicates \(\) are highly saturated, as illustrated in the Appendix.

